OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1775426988
OL,3,CTravel disruption and high winds as
OL,4,CStorm Dave batters North West
OL,6,FThe highest gusts of 71 mph were
OL,7,Frecorded in Blackpool with wind speeds
OL,8,Fon the Isle of Man recorded at 66 mph
OL,10,FThe strongest gust overnight was 93mph
OL,11,Fat Capel Curig in North Wales,
OL,13,FA Met Office spokesperson said: "The
OL,14,Fwinds eased down a bit more quickly
OL,15,Fthan forecast across Scotland,
OL,16,Fnorthern England and Wales.
OL,18,F"Storm Dave is pulling away and the
OL,19,Fwarnings are easing more quickly than
OL,20,Fforecast so the yellow warnings were
OL,21,Fno longer warranted."
